cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the groupcast index coding problem, which is a problem in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the construction of algorithms and lower bounds, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with matrices and linear codes, which could place it in cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
